WEBVTT

01:08.618 --> 01:10.254
<i>Frank always used to say,</i>

01:10.321 --> 01:12.189
<i>"Tell your story walkin',
pal."</i>

01:12.256 --> 01:15.692
<i>He was more philosophical
than your average gumshoe,</i>

01:15.759 --> 01:18.029
<i>but he liked to do his talkin'
on the move,</i>

01:18.095 --> 01:20.364
<i>so here's how
it all went down.</i>

01:20.431 --> 01:22.665
<i>I got somethin' wrong
with my head.</i>

01:22.732 --> 01:24.001
<i>That's the first thing
to know.</i>

01:24.068 --> 01:25.202
If!

01:25.269 --> 01:26.770
<i>It's like having glass
in the brain.</i>

01:26.836 --> 01:29.240
<i>I can't stop
pickin' things apart...</i>

01:29.306 --> 01:32.009
<i>twistin' 'em around,
reassembling 'em.</i>

01:32.076 --> 01:34.378
<i>Words and sounds, especially.</i>

01:34.445 --> 01:36.480
<i>It's like an itch
that has to be scratched.</i>

01:36.546 --> 01:39.883
Quit pullin' at it. You're gonna
make a fuckin' mess out of things.

01:41.485 --> 01:43.887
I got threads in my heads.

01:43.954 --> 01:46.490
I got threads in my heads!

01:46.556 --> 01:48.325
I got threads in my heads,
man!

01:50.227 --> 01:51.495
<i>And I twitch a lot.</i>

01:51.561 --> 01:52.929
<i>It's hard to miss.</i>

01:52.997 --> 01:54.965
<i>It makes me look
like a goddamn spastic,</i>

01:55.032 --> 01:57.834
<i>but if I try to hold it back,
it just makes it worse.</i>

01:57.901 --> 01:59.036
Ah.

01:59.103 --> 02:01.272
Shit, just help me out,
will ya?

02:01.338 --> 02:04.008
Like I said, a fuckin' mess!

02:04.075 --> 02:06.843
Jesus, Freakshow,
ruin another sweater.

02:06.910 --> 02:08.877
No, cut it closer.
Cut it closer.

02:09.645 --> 02:11.748
<i>Fuckin' mess is right.</i>

02:11.815 --> 02:15.252
<i>The nun said my soul wasn't at peace
with God and I should do penance.</i>

02:15.319 --> 02:17.021
<i>Frank said anyone
teaching God's love</i>

02:17.088 --> 02:18.655
<i>while they hit you
with a stick</i>

02:18.721 --> 02:20.590
<i>should be ignored
on every subject.</i>

02:21.258 --> 02:22.892
<i>Frank Minna.</i>

02:22.960 --> 02:25.329
<i>If you had to pick just
one guy to be on your side,</i>

02:25.396 --> 02:26.964
<i>he's the one you'd want.</i>

02:27.031 --> 02:30.000
<i>It's Minna's game.
We're all just in the lineup.</i>

02:30.067 --> 02:31.135
- Boys.
- Boss.

02:31.202 --> 02:33.237
Frank.
Frankly Frankady Franko!

02:33.304 --> 02:34.637
All right, listen.

02:34.704 --> 02:37.208
Here's the shot.
I'll be up on the third floor.

02:37.274 --> 02:40.211
Lionel will go to the payphone
in about 20 minutes.

02:40.277 --> 02:42.645
When they come, probably
three or four of them,

02:42.712 --> 02:44.014
when they come,
you call me here.

02:44.081 --> 02:46.616
I'll buzz 'em in.
Coney waits at the door.

02:46.683 --> 02:48.718
I buzz him in,
he stays inside.

02:48.785 --> 02:50.521
Lionel's listening,
sharp on the line.

02:50.588 --> 02:53.857
If you hear me say, "We have
a problem," hustle over.

02:53.923 --> 02:57.094
Coney lets you in.
The two of you come upstairs,

02:57.161 --> 02:58.329
back me up quick.

02:58.395 --> 02:59.729
What's going down here, Frank?

03:01.065 --> 03:03.367
I gotta keep this
under my hat, boys.

03:03.434 --> 03:04.801
Fat cats in hats!

03:04.868 --> 03:06.237
Them's the ones, pal.

03:06.303 --> 03:08.838
Let's catch a big score
and get fat ourselves.

03:08.905 --> 03:10.840
- Boss, we're not carrying.
- What?

03:10.907 --> 03:12.977
A piece. I don't have a piece.

03:13.043 --> 03:15.513
"A piece"? Say "gun," Gilbert.

03:15.579 --> 03:18.015
- Okay, I don't have a gun.
- That's what I count on.

03:18.082 --> 03:21.385
That's how I sleep at night,
you with no gun.

03:21.452 --> 03:23.521
I got a gun. You just show up.

03:23.587 --> 03:24.654
I wouldn't want
you chuckleheads

03:24.721 --> 03:25.822
coming up a staircase

03:25.889 --> 03:27.224
with a hairpin
and a harmonica.

03:27.291 --> 03:29.926
Hairy chin, harmony harp!
Quit windin' me up.

03:29.994 --> 03:31.761
With an unlit cigar
and a chicken wing.

03:31.828 --> 03:32.963
- Right, Brooklyn?
- Chicky wing ding.

03:33.030 --> 03:34.365
I wing that chick in the ding.

03:34.431 --> 03:35.899
Come on, seriously.

03:35.966 --> 03:38.135
Don't throw me off.

03:38.202 --> 03:39.503
Just give us the rest of it,
all right?

03:39.570 --> 03:40.803
All right, all right.

03:40.870 --> 03:42.506
Now, if I say,
"Let me use the can,"

03:42.573 --> 03:43.873
it means we're comin' out.

03:43.940 --> 03:46.243
Get Gil, get in the car,
get ready to follow.

03:46.310 --> 03:49.079
I might need to give
someone the slip. Got it?

03:49.146 --> 03:50.381
Yeah. Problem up the stairs.

03:50.447 --> 03:52.383
"Use the can,"
start the car. Got it.

03:52.449 --> 03:53.951
Get, gotten, got, gotcha!

03:54.018 --> 03:55.586
Lionel's got it,
just follow his lead.

03:55.653 --> 03:57.488
Oh, come on,
you gotta be kiddin' me.

03:57.555 --> 04:00.324
Coney, what did I say when I came
into the office last Tuesday?

04:00.391 --> 04:02.226
- What?
- Lionel?

04:02.293 --> 04:04.328
You hung up your coat, you put
your hat on the third hook,

04:04.395 --> 04:05.596
you said, "I just saw
a girl on the ferry,

04:05.663 --> 04:06.896
and the smile she gave me

04:06.964 --> 04:08.399
is gonna get me
through the winter."

04:08.465 --> 04:09.667
Then you threw your notebook
to Danny, and said,

04:09.732 --> 04:11.068
"How's a guy supposed to keep

04:11.135 --> 04:12.303
a marriage together
with 22 on the menu?"

04:12.369 --> 04:14.371
Like I said,
Lionel's on point.

04:19.176 --> 04:20.511
Sit on it, Bailey!

04:20.577 --> 04:21.579
<i>Fuckin' Bailey.</i>

04:21.644 --> 04:22.946
If!

04:23.013 --> 04:24.448
<i>Bailey's what my head
calls me.</i>

04:24.515 --> 04:26.783
<i>It calls me out
whenever I try to resist it.</i>

04:26.849 --> 04:28.718
<i>There's things
that calm it down.</i>

04:28.785 --> 04:30.554
<i>Gum, weed.</i>

04:30.621 --> 04:33.224
<i>Sometimes, something a little
stronger if I'm in bad shape.</i>

04:33.290 --> 04:35.492
<i>But if I try to put
a lid on it, it gets worse.</i>

04:35.559 --> 04:37.361
<i>If I get nervous,
it gets worse.</i>

04:37.428 --> 04:39.163
<i>If I get excited,
it gets worse.</i>

04:39.230 --> 04:40.030
If!

04:40.097 --> 04:42.032
<i>It's the argument I can't win.</i>

04:42.099 --> 04:43.167
Hey!

04:44.801 --> 04:46.237
Another Minna classic.

04:46.303 --> 04:48.205
Freezin' our asses off.
Don't even know the score.

04:48.272 --> 04:50.708
- What, you have big plans this weekend, Coney?
- Yeah, maybe.

04:50.773 --> 04:53.177
- Hot date?
- Maybe. Maybe I do.

04:53.244 --> 04:54.645
Coney Island!

04:54.712 --> 04:56.247
Coney Island hot dogs!

04:56.313 --> 04:58.015
Coney Island hot dogs
right here!

04:58.082 --> 05:00.551
All right, Freakshow,
just a little quieter, please.

05:03.853 --> 05:05.356
That's it. We're on.
Be ready.

05:22.172 --> 05:23.674
- Hey.
- <i>Hey, boss.</i>

05:23.741 --> 05:25.442
Bossy, bossy bitch!

05:25.509 --> 05:27.077
<i>You keeping it together,
Brooklyn?</i>

05:27.144 --> 05:29.113
No, no, no.
I got my gum.

05:29.179 --> 05:30.847
I'll keep it under control
when it counts.

05:30.913 --> 05:33.050
Like we said,
stay tuned in, pal.

05:33.117 --> 05:34.618
I might need
that head of yours later.

05:34.685 --> 05:36.186
<i>Yeah, I got you covered, boss.</i>

05:36.253 --> 05:39.089
I know you do.

05:43.160 --> 05:45.763
Hey, I think
your friends are here.

05:45.828 --> 05:47.564
<i>All right, how many?</i>

05:47.631 --> 05:49.233
<i>There's two walkin' up
the block, two out the car.</i>

05:50.267 --> 05:52.703
- <i>You see 'em?</i>
- Yeah, I see 'em.

05:52.770 --> 05:56.073
Jesus Christ,
look at the size of that guy.

05:56.140 --> 05:58.409
They got... They got
serious muscle with them.

05:58.475 --> 05:59.510
Is everything cool, boss?

05:59.576 --> 06:02.845
Cool as can be.
Just a little chat.

06:06.317 --> 06:08.952
<i>"Here lies
Frank Minna. Cool as can be."</i>

06:09.019 --> 06:11.622
<i>They'll carve that on his fuckin' tombstone.</i>

06:11.689 --> 06:13.757
<i>I don't know if it was
growin' up in Greenpoint</i>

06:13.823 --> 06:15.392
<i>or fightin' the Japanese,</i>

06:15.459 --> 06:18.195
<i>but he was cool under pressure
in a way you can't teach.</i>

06:18.262 --> 06:20.364
<i>I was just happy to
have a job on his team.</i>

06:20.431 --> 06:23.833
<i>And if there's one thing my
pain-in-the-ass brain does know how to do,</i>

06:23.900 --> 06:25.336
<i>it's listen
and remember things.</i>

06:30.274 --> 06:33.177
Gentlemen,
thanks for coming. Drink?

06:33.243 --> 06:34.745
We're not gonna
be here that long.

06:34.812 --> 06:36.113
Now explain this crap.

06:36.180 --> 06:37.581
Which part
didn't you understand?

06:37.648 --> 06:39.817
<i>How about the part
where you got the idea</i>

06:39.882 --> 06:41.385
<i>to go poking around after some
colored broad, for starters?</i>

06:41.452 --> 06:42.820
<i>She works for the committee.</i>

06:42.885 --> 06:44.088
She's a fuckin' secretary.

06:44.154 --> 06:45.489
We told you
to dig in on Horowitz,

06:45.556 --> 06:46.824
find something
we can shut them down with.

06:46.889 --> 06:48.225
There's nothing there, Lou.

06:48.292 --> 06:50.427
<i>You wanna know what's goin' on
in that report,</i>

06:50.494 --> 06:52.830
<i>that "colored broad" is doing most
of the legwork on Hamilton for 'em.</i>

06:52.895 --> 06:54.897
So I put some time
into that, too.

06:54.965 --> 06:56.400
You looked in
some funny places.

06:56.467 --> 06:59.069
What can I tell ya?
I'm a snoop. It's what I do.

06:59.136 --> 07:00.204
It's called being thorough.

07:00.270 --> 07:01.405
It's called
wasting our time.

07:01.472 --> 07:03.006
This is fucking Chinese,
Frank!

07:03.073 --> 07:04.475
If you need a roadmap
to wipe your ass,

07:04.541 --> 07:05.609
I can't help you, Lou.

07:05.676 --> 07:07.010
Walk us through it,
Mr. Minna,

07:07.077 --> 07:08.612
just to be sure
we're very clear.

07:08.679 --> 07:10.114
It's right there in ink.

07:21.191 --> 07:24.161
<i>Anybody else like to
offer a different interpretation?</i>

07:24.228 --> 07:25.662
<i>None of this
can be proved.</i>

07:25.729 --> 07:27.097
<i>That signature
is the real deal.</i>

07:27.164 --> 07:28.499
If you knew the man,

07:28.565 --> 07:30.067
you'd know why that seems
highly implausible.

07:30.134 --> 07:31.001
I checked it
against the others.

07:31.068 --> 07:32.469
That is his John Hancock.

07:32.536 --> 07:34.071
And the paper trail
backs it up.

07:34.138 --> 07:34.937
Think Horowitz
knows all of this?

07:35.005 --> 07:36.240
No.

07:36.306 --> 07:37.775
<i>Or you'd already
be eating shit.</i>

07:37.841 --> 07:39.576
<i>It'd have been in the paper
the next day.</i>

07:39.643 --> 07:41.311
<i>The girl,
she married? Got family?</i>

07:41.378 --> 07:42.746
<i>It's all in my file.</i>

07:42.813 --> 07:44.481
<i>Her mother's dead.
No brother or sisters.</i>

07:44.548 --> 07:46.683
- What about her father?
- Father's a busted-up vet.

07:46.750 --> 07:49.520
He runs a jazz club up here.
He drinks too much.

07:49.586 --> 07:51.422
<i>Mr. Minna,
I'll assume</i>

07:51.488 --> 07:53.923
<i>you're aware of what occurs
a week from Thursday?</i>

07:53.991 --> 07:55.192
<i>I am.</i>

07:55.259 --> 07:56.593
So then,
you understand

07:56.660 --> 07:57.995
our firm determination
to keep such information

07:58.061 --> 07:59.530
out of the hands
of our detractors?

07:59.596 --> 08:01.131
<i>Sure,
it's the nature of the game.</i>

08:01.198 --> 08:02.633
<i>But these are all photos.</i>

08:02.699 --> 08:04.368
May I hope you're in
possession of the originals?

08:04.435 --> 08:06.203
- I am.
- Excellent.

08:06.270 --> 08:07.905
Well, we'll need to
get those from you.

08:07.971 --> 08:09.306
I figured as much.

08:09.373 --> 08:11.241
I thought we could
talk about terms.

08:11.308 --> 08:13.243
What the fuck
are you talkin' about?

08:14.711 --> 08:16.046
Have you lost your mind?

08:16.113 --> 08:17.881
Let's not kid
each other, fellas.

08:17.947 --> 08:20.150
You got the biggest gravy train
of the century pulling out.

08:20.217 --> 08:22.219
I'm just asking for a seat
here in the rear.

08:22.286 --> 08:23.554
That's quite impossible.

08:23.620 --> 08:25.656
I'd double this
at any paper in town.

08:27.691 --> 08:29.226
I'm gonna pretend
you didn't say

08:29.293 --> 08:30.561
what you just said,
and we're gonna get...

08:30.627 --> 08:31.795
<i>It's just an observation.</i>

08:31.862 --> 08:33.297
<i>I'm here in good faith.</i>

08:33.363 --> 08:34.631
- <i>Just assessing value...</i>
- <i>You can forget it!</i>

08:34.698 --> 08:36.265
Jeez, Lou.

08:36.332 --> 08:38.335
What is your beef with a guy
gettin' paid for good work?

08:38.402 --> 08:39.837
As far as I can see,
you get paid

08:39.903 --> 08:41.638
for doin' nothing.

08:41.705 --> 08:43.039
- <i>Watch your mouth.</i>
- <i>Jesus, take it easy.</i>

08:43.106 --> 08:44.241
- Shit.
- <i>Open up your coat.</i>

08:44.308 --> 08:45.709
- What?
- Are you carryin'?

08:45.776 --> 08:47.344
- You bring a gun to a meeting?
- I had it

08:47.411 --> 08:48.745
- since the war, Lou...
- What the fuck?

08:48.812 --> 08:50.280
Listen, motherfucker,
I'm gonna have my friend

08:50.347 --> 08:51.648
<i>shove that right up your ass.</i>

08:51.715 --> 08:52.883
<i>Enough.
Lou, a word.</i>

08:55.385 --> 08:58.188
Oh, come on, fellas,
don't get in a twist.

08:58.255 --> 08:59.490
It's just business.

08:59.556 --> 09:00.824
Mr. Minna,
we do appreciate

09:00.891 --> 09:02.259
the service you've rendered.

09:02.326 --> 09:03.527
And these gentlemen

09:03.594 --> 09:04.895
will take you
to get the originals

09:04.963 --> 09:06.396
and if all is in order,

09:06.463 --> 09:08.365
we'll arrange an appropriate
resolution for you.

09:08.432 --> 09:11.335
<i>Of course.
Like I say, good faith.</i>

09:11.401 --> 09:13.437
<i>Just let me use the can first.</i>

09:15.305 --> 09:17.674
Come on, come on!
Come on, come on!

09:19.142 --> 09:20.377
Shithead hitter!

09:20.444 --> 09:21.912
- Hit him in the shitter!
- What happened?

09:21.980 --> 09:23.614
They hit him. They hit him.
I think that they hit him.

09:23.680 --> 09:25.048
Well, Jesus, Freakshow,
what are we doing here?

09:25.115 --> 09:26.583
No, no, no. Wait, wait, wait.

09:26.650 --> 09:28.185
He said, "Use the can."
He wants us to follow him.

09:28.252 --> 09:30.787
Can the man!
Can the loose man!

09:35.859 --> 09:37.628
And this fucking guy.

09:40.130 --> 09:41.932
- I don't like it.
- Me, neither. Let's go.

09:43.100 --> 09:44.468
Shit!

09:52.142 --> 09:54.378
No, no. No.

09:54.444 --> 09:56.747
Shit. We gotta go,
we gotta go!

09:56.813 --> 09:58.649
Come on, come on, come on!

09:58.715 --> 10:00.350
Go, go, go! Fire it up!

10:00.417 --> 10:01.618
Fire it up, come on!

10:02.954 --> 10:04.588
This fucking guy!

10:04.655 --> 10:06.857
Eat me, Mr. Dickey Weed!

10:06.924 --> 10:09.059
Eat me, Mr. Dickey Weed!

10:11.094 --> 10:13.330
Come on.

10:13.397 --> 10:16.199
Left, left, left.
Lick me, Loose Lucy!

10:22.539 --> 10:23.907
There, there, there.
That's them. That's them.

10:23.975 --> 10:25.776
Don't blow past them,
don't blow past them.

10:25.842 --> 10:27.411
Slow down, slow down.

10:29.212 --> 10:31.748
Watch out! Watch out!

10:31.815 --> 10:33.183
Shit!

10:35.252 --> 10:37.187
You fuckin' blind?

10:49.533 --> 10:51.970
- The fuck?
- How'd we lose them?

10:52.036 --> 10:54.204
There, there! There!

11:00.310 --> 11:01.645
Where's he goin'?

11:01.712 --> 11:03.413
The ramp, he's goin'
to Queens. Queenie Coney.

11:03.480 --> 11:06.583
Queenie Coney. Queenie Coney.

11:06.650 --> 11:08.752
In the right lane.
Get to the right.

11:08.819 --> 11:10.120
Where the fuck are they?

11:17.361 --> 11:18.495
Son of a bitch, that's them!

11:18.562 --> 11:19.896
Come on,
we're gonna lose them.

11:20.497 --> 11:21.465
Come on!

11:21.531 --> 11:22.899
- Quacker, quoter, quarter!
- What?

11:22.967 --> 11:24.201
Quacker, quoter, quarter!

11:24.267 --> 11:25.435
- What?
- Quarter! You need a quarter!

11:25.502 --> 11:26.536
Get a fuckin' quarter out,
Coney!

11:26.603 --> 11:27.871
Why didn't you say something?

11:28.839 --> 11:31.208
Go, go, go! Go, go!

11:45.222 --> 11:46.823
There, there, there.
Go left, go left.

11:49.127 --> 11:50.394
They gotta be somewhere.

11:50.460 --> 11:53.664
I'd say they're somewhere,
Gil, yes. Where?

12:00.671 --> 12:02.706
Stop, go back! Go back!

12:02.773 --> 12:03.774
Jesus!

12:12.616 --> 12:14.484
Shit! Drop it!
We gotta get out of here!

12:14.551 --> 12:16.453
Come on, let's go!
Let's go!

12:16.520 --> 12:17.721
God damn it.

12:21.159 --> 12:22.359
Frank!

12:22.893 --> 12:23.961
Pull it up!

12:28.432 --> 12:29.833
You wanna
help me out here, please?

12:29.900 --> 12:32.502
- Yeah.
- Oh, shit!

12:32.569 --> 12:34.938
- Can you stand?
- Yeah.

12:37.975 --> 12:40.310
Coney, you lug wrench,
get my hat!

12:40.377 --> 12:41.411
Forget the hat, Frank.

12:41.478 --> 12:42.946
Get my hat, you fucking mook.

12:44.915 --> 12:46.516
Get my gun, too.

12:51.722 --> 12:52.957
Where the hell
are you going?

12:53.024 --> 12:54.491
I don't know around here.

12:54.558 --> 12:55.659
- Give me something.
- Well, head for the hospital.

12:55.726 --> 12:57.294
Jesus!
Hospitable herpetologist!

12:57.360 --> 12:58.462
Mercy Hospital.

12:58.528 --> 13:00.430
Up McGuinness,
you cabbageheads!

13:02.299 --> 13:03.934
- Ah, sorry.
- Pay attention!

13:04.001 --> 13:05.535
- If, if!
- Easy, pal.

13:05.602 --> 13:06.870
Sorry. Sorry.

13:06.937 --> 13:08.839
Put my watch and my wallet
in my hat

13:08.905 --> 13:09.840
and leave it in the car.

13:09.906 --> 13:10.975
Don't want anybody
stealin' it.

13:11.042 --> 13:12.676
The fuck happened, Frank?

13:12.743 --> 13:14.277
I took 'em on a wild goose
chase and I tried to slip 'em.

13:14.344 --> 13:15.579
Ah, we should have
jumped in sooner.

13:15.645 --> 13:16.981
I thought
you were signaling me off.

13:17.048 --> 13:18.949
