behind him when he said it</i>

29:45.970 --> 29:47.571
<i>and she knew
they weren't bluffin'.</i>

29:47.637 --> 29:50.307
<i>After that,
I was in their crew.</i>

29:56.047 --> 29:57.247
If!

30:10.460 --> 30:12.295
- L&L.
- <i>Who am I speaking to?</i>

30:12.696 --> 30:14.564
Ass-rog!

30:14.631 --> 30:16.500
This is Lionel Essrog.
I'm associate...

30:16.566 --> 30:18.535
Hello?

30:28.079 --> 30:29.613
Formosa.

30:30.280 --> 30:31.681
Formosa.

30:34.417 --> 30:35.919
<i>Frank was just
from the neighborhood.</i>

30:35.987 --> 30:37.255
<i>He was smart.</i>

30:37.320 --> 30:38.588
<i>Everybody knew
he was goin' places.</i>

30:38.655 --> 30:39.991
<i>Everybody liked him.</i>

30:40.057 --> 30:42.093
For my ass, Bailey!

30:42.160 --> 30:43.827
<i>He was friends
with one of the priests,</i>

30:43.894 --> 30:46.463
<i>and he heard I had a thing
for remembering.</i>

30:46.530 --> 30:48.565
<i>Numbers and words and things,</i>

30:48.632 --> 30:51.068
<i>and he had uses for that.</i>

30:51.135 --> 30:53.737
<i>He was the one that taught me
how to use my head,</i>

30:53.804 --> 30:55.772
<i>get it under control,
make it work for me.</i>

30:57.241 --> 30:59.843
<i>He took all of us
under his wing, eventually.</i>

30:59.910 --> 31:02.579
<i>Gave us a place
in this shitty world.</i>

31:20.298 --> 31:21.299
- Lionel?
- If!

31:21.364 --> 31:23.366
Oh, Jesus Christ!

31:23.433 --> 31:24.768
You scared the hell out of me.

31:24.835 --> 31:26.170
I thought
I was lookin' at a ghost.

31:26.237 --> 31:28.538
- What are you doin'?
- Spinnin'.

31:28.605 --> 31:30.640
- You back already?
- Nah, I'm on a round trip.

31:30.707 --> 31:32.409
I gotta go back soon.

31:32.909 --> 31:34.511
You okay?

31:34.578 --> 31:37.480
I should have never let him
get in that car.

31:37.547 --> 31:39.050
I think I blew it, Danny.

31:39.116 --> 31:41.751
I had a sergeant once
in the Bulge. Told me,

31:41.818 --> 31:43.887
"Sometimes you do everything
you're supposed to,

31:43.955 --> 31:46.656
and it all still goes
to shit." Hmm?

31:47.390 --> 31:49.060
It ain't on you, bud.

31:49.126 --> 31:50.493
Thanks, D.

31:51.062 --> 31:52.096
Any calls?

31:53.030 --> 31:54.397
Yeah. Oh, shit!

31:56.000 --> 31:57.068
I gotta go.

31:57.134 --> 31:58.468
I got a 2:30.

31:59.836 --> 32:01.239
Hey...

32:01.305 --> 32:03.975
did you ever hear Frank mention
anything about "Formosa"?

32:04.041 --> 32:05.142
Like the Jap island?

32:05.209 --> 32:07.544
Nah. He was wounded
and out before then.

32:08.179 --> 32:09.579
Hmm.

32:09.646 --> 32:12.549
There is that joint, Formosa,
in, uh, Midtown.

32:12.616 --> 32:15.152
I took Linda there
to see Chet Baker once.

32:18.022 --> 32:19.522
<i>Frank didn't have
to cover for me.</i>

32:19.589 --> 32:21.491
<i>He just never put me
into situations</i>

32:21.558 --> 32:23.327
<i>that were gonna
punch my buttons.</i>

32:23.393 --> 32:26.097
<i>Talkin' to people, gettin'
information out of 'em,</i>

32:26.163 --> 32:27.831
<i>that's the bread and butter
of the trade,</i>

32:27.898 --> 32:29.666
<i>but never my strong suit.</i>

32:29.733 --> 32:32.236
<i>Especially if a girl shows up
in the mix</i>

32:32.303 --> 32:34.838
<i>and, in this line of work,
they usually do.</i>

32:34.905 --> 32:36.207
Music's at 7:00.

32:36.274 --> 32:38.608
Yeah, could I get
an early one? Whiskey, neat?

32:38.675 --> 32:40.610
- Irish?
- Sure.

32:40.677 --> 32:43.047
Say, are you in here regular?

32:43.114 --> 32:44.614
Most of my life.

32:44.681 --> 32:46.583
You ever seen this guy
come in?

32:46.650 --> 32:48.551
Name's Frank Minna.

32:48.618 --> 32:49.786
Seen him around?

32:49.853 --> 32:52.356
Everybody looks like
everybody to me,

32:52.422 --> 32:54.158
but I don't think so.

32:54.225 --> 32:55.592
She's good with faces.

32:56.961 --> 32:58.162
Seen that guy?

32:58.229 --> 32:59.729
- Friend of yours?
- Yeah.

33:01.198 --> 33:02.967
- Nice face.
- If!

33:04.601 --> 33:06.003
Nice yourself.

33:06.971 --> 33:08.205
You got a light?

33:15.779 --> 33:17.847
A tease.

33:20.583 --> 33:21.785
Sorry.

33:25.655 --> 33:28.625
Jesus. Forget I asked.

33:28.692 --> 33:31.963
- Ass-talk, Bailey!
- Classy!

33:32.029 --> 33:34.531
You got somethin'
against blondes?

33:34.597 --> 33:37.901
It's gotta sound right
or I can't stop doing it.

33:38.601 --> 33:40.438
Must be inconvenient.

33:40.503 --> 33:43.873
Buddy, you don't know
the half of it.

33:43.940 --> 33:46.110
That uptown shit's
the real deal, huh?

33:46.177 --> 33:47.811
You get up there much?

33:47.877 --> 33:49.313
- Sorry?
- King Rooster.

33:49.380 --> 33:51.848
- I don't know it.
- Jazz joint in Harlem.

33:51.915 --> 33:53.384
Lucky's is a good time, too,

33:53.451 --> 33:54.718
but all the guys playing hard
are at the Rooster.

33:57.687 --> 33:58.990
Thanks a lot.

34:18.309 --> 34:19.641
We ain't open yet.

34:19.708 --> 34:21.643
Yeah, could I get
an early one? I'm freezin'.

34:23.981 --> 34:26.083
I'll take a whiskey, neat.
Keep it.

34:28.252 --> 34:29.753
Hey, you the manager?

34:29.819 --> 34:32.123
I look like the manager?

34:32.922 --> 34:33.991
Who's playin' tonight?

34:34.058 --> 34:36.559
Hey, Billy, who's on tonight?

34:36.626 --> 34:38.129
Mr. Bigshot.

34:38.195 --> 34:39.795
I hope they don't
think they drinkin' free.

34:39.862 --> 34:41.598
Well, you know they do.

34:41.664 --> 34:43.533
You know who's
gonna say somethin' about that.

34:43.600 --> 34:44.801
You caught this cat?

34:45.768 --> 34:47.271
I seen cool.

34:47.338 --> 34:49.106
This brother rewritin' cool.

34:49.172 --> 34:51.541
- I'll catch him next time.
- Don't wait long.

34:51.608 --> 34:53.511
These French girls
keep lovin' him up,

34:53.576 --> 34:54.744
he's gonna move over there
for good.

34:54.811 --> 34:56.612
French kissin' cats!

34:57.148 --> 34:58.215
Thanks, pal.

35:05.822 --> 35:07.358
<i>On my average day,</i>

35:07.425 --> 35:08.892
<i>the weed will handle
my twitching and shouting,</i>

35:08.959 --> 35:10.760
<i>let me get to sleep.</i>

35:10.827 --> 35:14.298
<i>But it makes
my thinking fuzzy.</i>

35:14.365 --> 35:18.102
<i>In my dreams, I'm calm and clear
like I was when I was a kid.</i>

35:19.836 --> 35:21.938
<i>Even after my head
started messin' with me,</i>

35:22.006 --> 35:24.141
<i>my mother
could settle it down.</i>

35:24.208 --> 35:25.775
<i>She'd sing soft songs,</i>

35:25.842 --> 35:27.311
<i>stroke the back of my neck,</i>

35:27.378 --> 35:29.746
<i>and it would leave me
for a while.</i>

35:29.813 --> 35:31.315
<i>We'd lie on the bed,</i>

35:31.382 --> 35:33.783
<i>talk about all the places
we were gonna go.</i>

35:52.136 --> 35:55.973
That "colored broad" is doing
most of the legwork on Hamilton for 'em.

35:59.876 --> 36:02.546
Christ, Coney,
did you get the shot or not?

36:02.612 --> 36:04.448
What? Doing what?

36:04.515 --> 36:07.084
Gettin' the... Gettin'
the paper ain't worth shit.

36:07.151 --> 36:08.852
The fuck's got to do
with his back?

36:08.918 --> 36:10.321
"Bendin' over," my ass.

36:10.387 --> 36:12.123
Look, I need him
liftin' the lawnmower

36:12.189 --> 36:13.823
out of the car
or playin' tennis,

36:13.890 --> 36:16.293
or spinnin' around the room
with some broad

36:16.360 --> 36:18.195
up on his tent pole
and his arms out wide.

36:18.262 --> 36:20.797
I don't give a shit as long as
it involves his back.

36:21.565 --> 36:22.765
Yeah.

36:22.832 --> 36:24.068
I know he's fakin' it, Gil.

36:24.135 --> 36:26.036
That's why he's won
three claims.

36:26.103 --> 36:28.905
Look, just wait him out
or set him up.

36:28.973 --> 36:32.076
I know it's cold. That's why
they call it winter!

36:32.143 --> 36:33.978
Fuck.

36:34.044 --> 36:35.446
I'm givin' him
till the end of the week.

36:35.513 --> 36:38.015
Hell, the guy could
lift a cow into a truck...

36:38.082 --> 36:39.849
Coney's still gonna
miss the shot.

36:39.916 --> 36:41.519
He still can't remember
to wind the film.

36:41.585 --> 36:43.053
He thinks it's a Tommy gun.

36:43.120 --> 36:45.822
I keep tellin' him, "Click,
advance. Click, advance."

36:45.889 --> 36:47.591
Can it! I'm givin' him
the rest of the week.

36:49.059 --> 36:51.761
Give me a fuckin' break, Gil.
What?

36:51.828 --> 36:53.830
Oh. Yeah, no, excuse me.
L&L.

36:53.897 --> 36:55.566
- We gettin' any rides?
- No.

36:55.633 --> 36:58.668
Nobody ever needs a ride on
Tuesday, you ever notice that?

36:58.735 --> 37:00.304
Never. What is that about?

37:00.371 --> 37:01.871
Tits on a Tuesday!

37:01.938 --> 37:03.107
Okay, thank you.

37:03.706 --> 37:04.707
Job?

37:04.774 --> 37:06.277
For me.

37:06.343 --> 37:07.877
Well, don't go gettin'
all mysterious now, T.

37:07.944 --> 37:09.846
You ain't no Minna.

37:10.314 --> 37:11.881
Yet.

37:11.948 --> 37:13.951
I'm going to pick up a prescription
for my mother, clam brain.

37:14.018 --> 37:15.519
You want all the details?

37:15.586 --> 37:16.886
All right.

37:16.954 --> 37:18.622
I'm goin' out for coffee.
You want?

37:18.688 --> 37:19.722
Yeah, cream and sugar.

37:19.789 --> 37:21.458
Oh!

37:21.525 --> 37:23.160
Okay.

37:23.227 --> 37:25.728
Meet the new boss.

37:25.795 --> 37:27.164
Mmm-hmm.

37:27.231 --> 37:29.133
Hey, D, if it's slow,
you up for something?

37:29.200 --> 37:30.267
Like what?

37:31.602 --> 37:35.272
Will you go sit on that place
for me? It's up in Harlem.

37:35.339 --> 37:36.307
I don't know it.

37:36.373 --> 37:37.608
I think Frank was there
that day,

37:37.675 --> 37:38.976
or maybe the day before,

37:39.043 --> 37:40.777
but it was in his pants,
it was almost full.

37:40.843 --> 37:42.246
- Fullsie pants!
- Yeah, well,

37:42.313 --> 37:43.414
maybe he just stopped in

37:43.480 --> 37:45.082
- for a book of matches.
- I don't think so.

37:45.149 --> 37:46.450
He was talkin'
about the colored girl

37:46.517 --> 37:47.985
who found somethin'
they were unhappy about,

37:48.052 --> 37:49.520
and he said her father's
a busted-up vet

37:49.587 --> 37:50.588
who runs a joint in Harlem,

37:50.654 --> 37:52.122
and this place is three blocks

37:52.189 --> 37:53.723
from where they had
that meeting.

37:53.790 --> 37:56.260
Mmm-hmm.
So, you went there?

37:56.327 --> 37:57.794
Yeah, and guess
who the manager is?

37:57.860 --> 37:59.463
He's a colored guy
with a bum arm.

37:59.530 --> 38:02.132
Oh, okay, what do you want me
to do about it?

38:02.199 --> 38:03.667
Just get in there, you know,

38:03.733 --> 38:05.935
see if you can get her name
off of them or something.

38:06.003 --> 38:08.372
Use your liquor board bit.
Lick Broader!

38:08.439 --> 38:09.673
I get her name.

38:09.739 --> 38:11.208
- That's it?
- No, sit there a while.

38:11.275 --> 38:12.942
See if she comes in.
Get her picture or somethin'.

38:13.010 --> 38:15.646
See if a colored girl
walks into a jazz joint?

38:15.713 --> 38:17.147
Let me make a prediction.

38:17.214 --> 38:19.016
Hey, asshole, I'm workin' it
from another angle, too.

38:19.083 --> 38:21.318
We'll put 'em together.
We'll figure out who she is.

38:21.385 --> 38:23.954
All right. Can I ask
why we're doin' this?

38:24.021 --> 38:25.689
'Cause he'd have
done it for us.

38:25.755 --> 38:26.991
You're right.

38:29.660 --> 38:31.562
Ah, it's fuckin' cold
for a sit.

38:31.629 --> 38:33.930
No, take the Bel Air.
That heater'll roast you like a brisket.

38:33.998 --> 38:34.999
Bet on the bris!

38:35.065 --> 38:36.500
What are you, a rabbi now?

38:36.567 --> 38:38.435
You don't want me handling
your bris, believe me.

38:56.220 --> 38:57.588
Can I help you?

38:57.655 --> 38:59.290
- Yeah. If!
- Bless you.

38:59.356 --> 39:00.958
Thank you.
I'm here to see Mildred.

39:01.025 --> 39:03.193
Mildred? There's nobody
by that name here.

39:03.260 --> 39:04.861
I'm pretty sure
it was Mildred.

39:04.927 --> 39:06.597
- Myrna.
- My mynah bird's Myrna.

39:06.664 --> 39:09.899
No. No, it was a colored girl
that I was speaking to.

39:10.734 --> 39:12.636
Uh... Josephine?

39:12.703 --> 39:14.505
Or Laura?

39:14.571 --> 39:15.739
- Mary.
- No,

39:15.838 --> 39:17.374
I'm pretty sure
it was Mildred.

39:17.441 --> 39:18.642
I was talking to her on
the phone about my application.

39:18.709 --> 39:19.809
What's your name?

39:19.876 --> 39:21.578
Betty.
What sort of application?

39:21.645 --> 39:24.148
For my vendor's license.

39:24.214 --> 39:25.783
Is this not
the licensing office?

39:25.848 --> 39:28.986
It's the Committee on Racial
Discrimination in Housing.

39:29.053 --> 39:30.120
Well, then,
you can't very well

39:30.187 --> 39:31.488
help me sell hot dogs,
can you?

39:31.555 --> 39:33.290
I'm so sorry.

39:33.357 --> 39:35.892
Wait. Mr. Horowitz
isn't here today, is he?

39:35.959 --> 39:38.162
- You mean Miss Horowitz?
- Either one.

39:38.228 --> 39:40.464
- She's in the back.
- Can you point her out to me?

39:41.031 --> 39:42.232
There she is.

39:42.865 --> 39:44.068
Hmm.

39:48.005 --> 39:49.939
You've been more helpful
than you know.

40:00.917 --> 40:02.052
We told you
to dig in on Horowitz.

40:02.119 --> 40:03.520
Horse a whip!

40:04.355 --> 40:05.556
Horse a whip!

40:45.696 --> 40:47.131
Shit, what happened?

40:47.197 --> 40:48.198
Jesus, Danny.

40:48.265 --> 40:49.867
Come on. All right.

40:49.932 --> 40:51.235
Come.

40:53.237 --> 40:55.339
Shit. You need ice?

40:55.406 --> 40:58.275
No, no. I'll take a shot.
You got one of those?

40:58.342 --> 40:59.343
Yeah.

41:01.345 --> 41:03.714
- Yeah, thanks.
- Who was it, D?

41:03.781 --> 41:04.982
Hmm.

41:06.949 --> 41:08.786
There was a couple of 'em.

41:08.852 --> 41:10.120
One was a giant.

41:10.187 --> 41:11.555
- A what?
- A fuckin' giant.

41:11.622 --> 41:13.657
I'm tellin' ya,
the biggest guy I ever saw.

41:13.724 --> 41:15.793
Worked me over pretty good.

41:15.859 --> 41:17.227
Murdered the camera.

41:17.294 --> 41:19.163
- Fuck. Did they say anything?
- Yeah.

41:19.229 --> 41:21.165
Uh... "Stay out
of Minna's garbage.

41:21.231 --> 41:22.699
Tell your crew the same."

41:22.766 --> 41:25.669
They had a big nasty knife
to my throat for that part.

41:25.736 --> 41:26.804
Those sons of bitches!

41:26.870 --> 41:29.406
But they didn't get this.

41:31.008 --> 41:32.409
- Assholes.
- The fuck is it?

41:32.476 --> 41:35.179
Giant-ass dog!
Ah, D, you're the tits.

41:35.245 --> 41:36.680
What are you two into?

41:48.258 --> 41:49.660
- You get 'em all?
- These are yours,

41:49.726 --> 41:51.428
- these are mine.
- Yeah.

41:52.029 --> 41:53.464
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

41:53.530 --> 41:55.532
- That's the same guy I saw.
- Yeah, yeah.

41:55.599 --> 41:57.401
- The bum arm.
- Forget all that, though.

41:57.468 --> 41:59.837
She doesn't show up till
sort of the end of the roll.

41:59.903 --> 42:01.171
Yeah.

42:01.238 --> 42:03.140
- Look, they come out together.
- Yeah.

42:03.207 --> 42:05.075
No, wait, but I saw her.
That's, uh...

42:05.142 --> 42:07.511
- Laura, they called her Laura.
- Laura Rose?

42:07.578 --> 42:09.646
Maybe that's Billy Rose,
if he's her father.

42:09.713 --> 42:12.082
She lives on the same corner
as the club.

42:12.149 --> 42:13.350
They must have made me early,

42:13.417 --> 42:14.651
as soon as I got out
to check it out,

42:14.718 --> 42:15.819
bam, they were on me.

42:15.886 --> 42:17.321
Yeah. That's her.

42:17.387 --> 42:20.190
That's the colored girl
that Frank was following.

42:20.257 --> 42:21.925
All right, I'm with you, okay?
It's just,

42:21.992 --> 42:23.627
- it's still a little thin.
- Skeletal.

42:23.694 --> 42:25.028
Thin? What?

42:25.095 --> 42:27.164
We already ID'd her.
We've been at it one day.

42:27.231 --> 42:29.533
Well, you know,
whatever it is, it's...

42:29.600 --> 42:33.103
It's gotta be big,
they're goin' this far, right?

42:33.170 --> 42:36.406
So, it's gotta be
worth something, then.

42:36.473 --> 42:38.542
I'll tell you what, Freakshow,
Gil and I,

42:38.609 --> 42:40.310
we'll stay on the money work,
just to keep us afloat,

42:40.377 --> 42:41.812
you and Danny
keep sniffin' this.

42:41.879 --> 42:42.880
Let's see what we get.

42:42.946 --> 42:44.047
- Fuck 'em!
- Yeah.

42:44.114 --> 42:45.315
- Right?
- Yeah.

42:45.382 --> 42:46.717
- If!
- I hope these mugs poke around

42:46.783 --> 42:48.185
'cause I got something
for them if they do.

42:48.252 --> 42:49.486
What do you say, D?

42:50.854 --> 42:52.122
Fellas, I...

42:52.856 --> 42:54.825
I loved him, you know.

42:54.892 --> 42:57.094
I mean, I'll, uh...

42:57.160 --> 42:59.296
I, uh...
I'll handle the car stuff.

42:59.363 --> 43:02.032
I'll work some domestic shit,

43:02.099 --> 43:03.433
but I got Linda.

43:03.500 --> 43:07.170
No, hey, hey,
that's the right thing.

43:07.237 --> 43:08.572
Get on home,

43:08.639 --> 43:10.274
- throw a steak on that eye.
- Yeah.

43:10.340 --> 43:12.376
I'll give you a lift.

43:14.979 --> 43:17.180
- So long.
- Yeah, yeah.

43:20.417 --> 43:22.753
What do you mean,
it might be worth something?

43:22.819 --> 43:24.721
I don't know, I thought maybe
we'll get something out of it.

43:24.788 --> 43:26.423
I ain't looking to make a deal
with these fucks.

43:26.490 --> 43:27.992
Forget that, then.
Look, I'm just...

43:28.058 --> 43:30.360
Don't you think I wanna
find out who whacked Frank?

43:30.427 --> 43:31.395
Yeah.

43:31.461 --> 43:32.729
Just don't hold out on me,
okay?

43:32.796 --> 43:34.565
We're workin'
on this thing together.

43:34.631 --> 43:37.901
We find who did this,
and we square accounts.

43:37.969 --> 43:39.403
If you say so, yeah.

43:40.737 --> 43:42.172
Wanna get a beer?

43:42.239 --> 43:43.907
- Nah.
- Come on.

43:43.975 --> 43:45.275
Come on. Let's get a beer.

43:45.342 --> 43:46.777
Come on, let's get a beer.

43:46.843 --> 43:48.012
Okay, leave me alone,
leave me alone.

43:48.078 --> 43:50.048
All right.

43:50.113 --> 43:51.682
Don't stay up too late,
kemosabe.

44:44.267 --> 44:46.403
Give up the seat,
asshole!

44:46.470 --> 44:48.138
Give her the seat!

46:14.725 --> 46:16.094
Hey, Gabby, they're closed.

46:16.160 --> 46:17.427
Oh,
you gotta be kidding me!

46:17.494 --> 46:19.830
- Yes...
- At 3:30? Ugh.

47:01.638 --> 47:02.974
Hey, pal,
I'm new to this beat.

47:03.040 --> 47:04.374
What's the story here?

47:04.441 --> 47:06.409
Stories of injustice
and despair,

47:06.476 --> 47:07.844
nodding assurances,

47:07.911 --> 47:11.748
and back to business as usual.
The American way.

47:11.815 --> 47:13.750
Though this one
could make things interesting.

47:13.817 --> 47:16.853
Hey, who's the, uh,
guy on the far right?

47:16.920 --> 47:18.655
It's Brooklyn
borough president.

47:18.722 --> 47:20.224
What are you,
a television reporter?

47:20.290 --> 47:21.491
No, just new.

47:21.558 --> 47:22.960
We'll commence
this public comment.

47:23.027 --> 47:25.196
State your name, address,
and affiliation, please.

47:25.263 --> 47:26.496
I'm William Lieberman,

47:26.563 --> 47:27.999
Mayor's Commission
on Slum Clearance.

47:28.065 --> 47:30.433
We'll arrange an appropriate
resolution for you.

47:30.500 --> 47:31.802
Resident of East...

47:31.868 --> 47:32.936
- Lieberman.
- ...65th Street, Manhattan.

47:35.806 --> 47:39.309
Cindy Fleming,
homemaker, Yonkers.

47:39.376 --> 47:40.877
Formerly East Tremont.

47:40.944 --> 47:42.679
My family was forced to move
when they seized

47:42.746 --> 47:44.714
our building for the Bronx
Expressway and I want

47:44.781 --> 47:46.316
- people to know that...
- Mrs. Horowitz.

47:46.383 --> 47:47.784
Miss.

47:47.851 --> 47:50.087
Miss Horowitz, you may not
hijack these proceedings

47:50.154 --> 47:51.755
- to air out old complaints...
- Gabby Horowitz,

47:51.822 --> 47:53.291
Committee for Racial
Discrimination in Housing,

47:53.356 --> 47:55.759
552 Clinton Avenue, Brooklyn.

47:55.826 --> 47:57.261
I thought that this was
a community hearing?

47:57.327 --> 47:58.728
On housing, not highways.

47:58.795 --> 48:00.630
You're making the same
promises to Fort Greene

48:00.697 --> 48:02.399
you made in East Tremont,

48:02.465 --> 48:05.303
where your so-called
"relocation services"

48:05.368 --> 48:06.837
vanished into thin air

48:06.903 --> 48:09.573
and left families like
the Flemings utterly adrift.

48:09.639 --> 48:11.175
People have a right to know
what they're in for.

48:11.242 --> 48:14.078
We are totally committed
to the welfare of families

48:14.145 --> 48:15.412
displaced by necessary

48:15.478 --> 48:17.514
community improvement programs

48:17.581 --> 48:21.085
and the past has been
instructive, miss,

48:21.152 --> 48:22.686
but our new contractors

48:22.752 --> 48:24.888
will ensure
all find adequate homes...

48:24.956 --> 48:26.756
This isn't Long Island,
you know.

48:26.823 --> 48:28.558
It's not just a blank canvas

48:28.625 --> 48:30.027
you can paint on
anywhere you like.

48:30.094 --> 48:33.197
There are people here,
established communities.

48:34.332 --> 48:35.665
Bill, if I may...

48:35.732 --> 48:37.601
I hope you all know my name.
I'm the mayor,

48:37.667 --> 48:39.603
newly residing
in Gracie Mansion.

48:40.370 --> 48:41.638
Uh, Miss Horowitz,

48:41.705 --> 48:44.108
thank you for your work
and your passion.

48:44.175 --> 48:45.575
Surely we can all agree that

48:45.642 --> 48:47.811
even in a city as great
as ours we have slums,

48:47.878 --> 48:50.881
and that slums are not to be
romanticized or preserved.

48:50.947 --> 48:52.116
You tear them down

48:52.183 --> 48:53.383
and improve quality of life
for everyone...

48:53.450 --> 48:55.719
A neighborhood is not a slum,

48:55.785 --> 48:57.088
because poor people
and minorities

48:57.154 --> 48:59.623
live there, Mr. Mayor.

48:59.689 --> 49:02.226
East Tremont wasn't a slum,

49:02.293 --> 49:03.995
Third Avenue wasn't a slum,

49:04.061 --> 49:06.596
and Fort Greene isn't a slum,
either.

49:06.663 --> 49:08.698
These are working-class
communities.

49:08.765 --> 49:12.103
Your developers are making
them slums, Mr. Randolph!

49:12.169 --> 49:14.905
That is unsubstantiated
and unmitigated bunk!

49:14.972 --> 49:16.539
We have
got it on paper.

49:16.606 --> 49:17.975
We got 20 people here tonight

49:18.042 --> 49:19.243
and scores behind them

49:19.310 --> 49:22.545
who can testify to
a scandalous fraud underway.

49:22.612 --> 49:23.981
Which way
do you want it first?

49:26.317 --> 49:27.450
Hey, hey, hey!

49:27.517 --> 49:28.885
We are embarking

49:28.953 --> 49:30.487
on the most ambitious
slum clearance program

49:30.553 --> 49:32.189
in American history,
Mrs. Horowitz,

49:32.256 --> 49:35.026
and you are gumming it up
with your molasses!

49:35.092 --> 49:36.793
A Niagara of molasses!

49:36.860 --> 49:39.030
Make him say his name!

49:39.096 --> 49:41.132
Name and place of residence
like everyone else!

49:41.198 --> 49:44.534
Now, see here, we all know
perfectly well who this is.

49:44.601 --> 49:46.404
Mo Randolph is one of our
greatest public servants.

49:46.469 --> 49:47.771
He's a living legend.

49:47.837 --> 49:50.374
Name and residence,
like everybody else!

49:50.473 --> 49:51.808
Shiver shitty self!

49:51.875 --> 49:53.910
He's led the Parks Department
for over 30 years.

49:53.978 --> 49:55.246
He's Commissioner
of Construction.

49:55.313 --> 49:56.780
He's got
too many jobs to name.

49:56.846 --> 49:59.116
And he lives right across
the street from me on 88th.

49:59.183 --> 50:01.085
Make him say it!

50:01.152 --> 50:02.552
So, let's stick to the
issues concerning the citizens of...

50:02.619 --> 50:04.121
Name, address!

50:04.188 --> 50:05.122
See here now,
if we can't keep this civil...

50:05.189 --> 50:06.257
Say it!

50:06.324 --> 50:08.292
...we'll have to ask you
to leave!

50:08.359 --> 50:09.559
Say it!

50:10.428 --> 50:11.429
Hey!

50:16.566 --> 50:19.303
Two fuckin' pigs in a blanket!
Ow!

50:19.370 --> 50:21.938
Hey! Say it, Hammy House Head!

50:22.006 --> 50:25.176
Say it! Say it! Say it!

50:30.680 --> 50:32.882
I got a condition.
Easy!

50:33.683 --> 50:35.485
"Hammy Ham House Head"?

50:35.552 --> 50:37.154
That's good.
I gotta remember that one.

50:37.221 --> 50:38.655
- If!
- Yeah, well,

50:38.722 --> 50:41.491
that's the rub in life,
all right, if. If only.

50:41.558 --> 50:42.926
Hey...

50:42.994 --> 50:44.594
You know things about
that guy, Bill Lieberman?

50:44.661 --> 50:45.929
Is he in charge of
this whole housing deal?

50:45.997 --> 50:47.731
Charge?
No, he's not in charge.

50:47.797 --> 50:49.899
More in charge than that guy
calling himself the mayor,

50:49.967 --> 50:52.635
but they all work for Moses.

50:54.238 --> 50:55.839
Hey, hey, stop, stop,
wait a second.

50:55.905 --> 50:57.574
- Let me go. You nuts?
- You just said Formosa.

50:57.640 --> 50:59.043
- What is that?
- What's Formosa?

50:59.110 --> 51:00.810
You said, "Working Formosa."
What does that mean?

51:00.877 --> 51:03.546
No, Jesus, I said, "They're
all working for Moses."

51:03.613 --> 51:05.249
Moses Randolph.

51:06.583 --> 51:08.319
Mo Randolph?
The guy who walked in late?

51:08.386 --> 51:11.055
He who will not speak his name
like one of the rabble.

51:11.122 --> 51:12.189
What do you care?

51:12.256 --> 51:13.857
Hey, hey, um...

51:13.923 --> 51:16.293
I'm Jake Gleason.
I'm with the <i>Post.</i>

51:16.360 --> 51:18.661
Can I buy you a cup of coffee?

51:18.728 --> 51:21.298
I'm hungry.
You can buy me dinner.

51:23.700 --> 51:24.901
Okay,
that means the one guy

51:24.969 --> 51:26.303
answers to the other guy,
but they all

51:26.370 --> 51:27.737
- gotta answer to the mayor.
- The mayor?

51:27.804 --> 51:29.140
That clown is so green,

51:29.206 --> 51:31.075
he doesn't even know
what he doesn't know yet.

51:31.142 --> 51:33.543
He'll be out the door
before he even realizes

51:33.610 --> 51:35.079
that every person
he turns to for advice

51:35.146 --> 51:36.679
- is on Randolph's payroll.
- I thought he was

51:36.746 --> 51:38.215
- the parks commissioner.
- He is.

51:38.282 --> 51:39.716
But they called him
the construction commissioner

51:39.783 --> 51:41.052
- in there.
- He's that, too, now,

51:41.118 --> 51:42.786
but they didn't even
have that position

51:42.852 --> 51:45.222
until the Feds decided
to get in the housing game.

51:45.289 --> 51:46.856
There was no defined power,

51:46.923 --> 51:49.126
so he defined it,
they approved it

51:49.193 --> 51:50.294
and now how much control

51:50.361 --> 51:51.895
over that money
has the city got? Zero.

51:51.962 --> 51:53.264
He's got it all. You know

51:53.330 --> 51:54.798
- what "eminent domain" is?
- I think, yeah...

51:54.864 --> 51:57.334
Yeah, if he says it's a slum,
it goes.

51:57.401 --> 51:58.802
He used to have to fight

51:58.868 --> 52:00.438
to put his highways and parks
where he wanted,

52:00.504 --> 52:02.672
and now, he goes anywhere,
tears anything down.

52:02.739 --> 52:05.742
He can condemn
a whole section of the city,

52:05.809 --> 52:06.810
evict everyone
who lives there,

52:06.876 --> 52:08.112
and put up what he wants.

52:08.179 --> 52:09.779
And he'll go at it
with an axe.

52:09.846 --> 52:11.182
Smacks with an axe!

52:11.248 --> 52:12.816
But he'd be the most
hated guy in the city.

52:12.882 --> 52:14.318
I mean,
he'd piss everybody off.

52:14.385 --> 52:15.819
They love him.

52:16.653 --> 52:18.556
That's what makes me so...

52:18.621 --> 52:21.058
He flies above it.
They revere him.

52:21.125 --> 52:24.061
- Why?
- Because he built the parks.

52:24.128 --> 52:27.331
As long as you're the guy
that brings people parks,

52:27.398 --> 52:29.599
you walk with the angels,
you can't lose.

52:29.666 --> 52:31.268
The day that
Rockaway Beach opened,

52:31.335 --> 52:34.071
Moses Randolph became
a folk hero in this town.

52:34.138 --> 52:36.673
People don't realize
how much he hates them.

52:36.739 --> 52:39.609
"The hero of the public
who hates people."

52:39.676 --> 52:40.844
That's your headline.

52:40.910 --> 52:43.947
And you know
who he hates especially?

52:44.014 --> 52:45.015
Negroes.

52:45.082 --> 52:46.749
He's going to seize
every neighborhood

52:46.816 --> 52:48.352
in this city that's not white

52:48.419 --> 52:50.955
and turn it over to his
handpicked private developers.

52:51.021 --> 52:52.223
So, you're saying
he's getting rich,

52:52.289 --> 52:53.790
he's taking kickbacks
on all this?

52:53.857 --> 52:55.392
No, he doesn't want money.
He wants control.

52:55.459 --> 52:58.162
And he brokers money
to get it and guard it.

52:58.229 --> 53:01.232
Some guys aren't satisfied
unless they have filet mignon.

53:01.298 --> 53:04.034
Moses Randolph
would be satisfied

53:04.101 --> 53:06.504
with a pastrami sandwich
and power.

53:06.570 --> 53:08.771
Hey, uh, excuse me.

53:08.838 --> 53:10.007
Could I get
a slice of cheesecake?

53:10.074 --> 53:11.375
Could you make it warm?

53:11.442 --> 53:12.909
I'd like it warm.

53:12.977 --> 53:15.879
Half the city is getting
a ride on one of his horses.

53:15.945 --> 53:17.414
For God's sakes, he controls

53:17.481 --> 53:19.483
every fuckin' construction job
in the city.

53:19.550 --> 53:21.651
But you said they just
created the position.

53:21.718 --> 53:23.954
No. Construction,
slums, parks.

53:24.021 --> 53:25.189
He's got 14 appointments.

53:25.256 --> 53:27.224
It's all just ink
on a glass door.

53:27.291 --> 53:29.226
None of it matters.
It's all BA.

53:29.293 --> 53:30.793
BA?

53:30.860 --> 53:33.030
Borough Authority.

53:33.097 --> 53:35.599
You call yourself a reporter?
On what?

53:35.665 --> 53:37.268
- The arts beat?
- Beet farts!

53:37.334 --> 53:39.036
- You read Emerson?
- No, should I?

53:39.103 --> 53:41.938
- Yeah, you fucking should.
- All right.

53:42.006 --> 53:45.042
Emerson said that
"an institution

53:45.109 --> 53:47.978
is the lengthened shadow
of one man."

53:48.045 --> 53:50.314
<i>This town is run
by the Borough Authority</i>

53:50.381 --> 53:54.185
<i>and the Borough Authority
is Moses Randolph.</i>

54:03.227 --> 54:04.428
If!

54:41.332 --> 54:42.399
Fucking Lieberman.

54:42.466 --> 54:44.101
If!

54:54.311 --> 54:55.878
<i>That quack in the diner</i>

54:55.945 --> 54:57.648
<i>with pork chop
and peas in his beard</i>

54:57.715 --> 55:00.351
<i>was one of the most talented
engineers of his generation.</i>

55:00.417 --> 55:02.885
<i>Ivy League.
Big awards.</i>

55:02.953 --> 55:04.421
<i>Walkin' right next
to his brother</i>

55:04.488 --> 55:06.523
<i>toward being
someone important.</i>

55:06.590 --> 55:09.193
<i>Then, sometime
after the Crash, just...</i>

55:09.260 --> 55:10.094
<i>nothing.</i>

55:10.160 --> 55:12.963
<i>Like he got erased.</i>

55:13.030 --> 55:15.733
<i>Maybe it was bad luck,
maybe booze.</i>

55:15.798 --> 55:18.736
<i>There was all kinds of
casualties in those days.</i>

55:18.801 --> 55:20.337
Ladies and gentlemen,

55:20.404 --> 55:21.672
please welcome

55:21.739 --> 55:25.276
the president of the Gotham
Builders Association,

55:25.342 --> 55:28.379
Joe Pompano!

55:31.948 --> 55:33.783
Gotta show this
to Bill Lieberman.

55:33.850 --> 55:37.388
He's gonna want to see this before
Randolph speaks, believe me.

55:41.492 --> 55:42.925
Thank you. Thank you,

55:42.993 --> 55:45.895
ladies and gentlemen.
Please settle down

55:45.963 --> 55:48.732
and lend
your serious attention.

55:48.798 --> 55:50.100
Don't worry. We'll celebrate.

55:50.167 --> 55:53.570
We're gonna eat like
only we know how to eat.

55:53.637 --> 55:56.674
Tonight's celebration
is made very special

55:56.740 --> 55:58.375
by our guest of honor,

55:58.442 --> 55:59.942
a brother to our trade...

56:00.010 --> 56:01.378
- Hey, Gleason, right?
- Hey.

56:01.445 --> 56:02.945
...who would rightly be hailed
this country's

56:03.013 --> 56:04.615
- master builder...
- Nice threads.

56:04.682 --> 56:08.285
...or "the Great Dirt Mover"

56:08.352 --> 56:09.953
as he likes to be called.

56:10.020 --> 56:11.955
Don't let them see you
pull out a notebook.

56:12.022 --> 56:16.193
Tonight, it's
"Press: Forget about it."

56:16.260 --> 56:18.295
We'd have
to look to the Caesars

56:18.362 --> 56:22.566
and pharaohs to find men
with a scale of vision

56:22.633 --> 56:24.068
to compare with his.

56:24.134 --> 56:25.703
- A great man.
- If!

56:25.769 --> 56:27.237
A man of history,

56:27.304 --> 56:31.775
serving the people of
this city for over 25 years,

56:31.841 --> 56:34.678
Moses Randolph!

56:43.821 --> 56:46.623
Jeez, you'd think
Patton showed up.

56:46.690 --> 56:49.960
He pays one and a half times
union rate on all of his jobs.

56:50.027 --> 56:52.262
They'd pave over
their mothers for him.

56:53.497 --> 56:54.897
Thank you, Joe.

56:55.666 --> 56:58.168
Tonight, over 300 years

56:58.235 --> 57:00.437
since the founding
of this great city,

57:00.504 --> 57:04.208
we recommit ourselves
to the ancient truth

57:04.274 --> 57:06.477
that it is not knowledge,

57:06.543 --> 57:08.312
but action and enterprise

57:08.379 --> 57:12.516
which are the engine
and objective in life.

57:12.583 --> 57:14.418
Clever men come and go,

57:14.485 --> 57:18.188
but for every dozen of them
with their big ideas,

57:18.255 --> 57:21.058
there is not more than one
that can execute them.

57:21.891 --> 57:23.060
I look around this room,

57:23.127 --> 57:24.762
I don't see
a lot of bright boys

57:24.828 --> 57:28.565
or goodie-goodie progressives
with their paralyzing ideals.

57:31.135 --> 57:33.170
I see the men of my tribe.

57:34.138 --> 57:36.140
The men who get things done.

57:36.206 --> 57:38.908
The doers that make
this country great!

57:41.845 --> 57:43.747
To be honored by you

57:43.814 --> 57:47.951
is all the affirmation or
payment I shall ever seek.

57:48.952 --> 57:50.487
I celebrate you

57:51.388 --> 57:52.523
and I thank you.

57:52.589 --> 57:54.291
Hear, hear!

58:27.324 --> 58:28.559
I'll catch you
on the next one.

58:28.625 --> 58:29.626
All right.

59:01.492 --> 59:02.693
You finished it?

59:02.759 --> 59:04.495
Best work I've done.

59:04.561 --> 59:08.131
A total modernization of
the state's electrical grid.

59:08.198 --> 59:11.201
And it's a scale
that only you can get done.

59:16.473 --> 59:17.808
Clean yourself up,
for Christ sakes.

59:17.875 --> 59:19.409
How? With what?

59:19.476 --> 59:21.144
Hey, not a fuckin' word
out of you about any of that.

59:21.211 --> 59:22.479
You bring that up to me
ever again,

59:22.546 --> 59:23.747
I'm gonna close you out
for good.

59:23.814 --> 59:25.349
Moses, I'm so far out,

59:25.415 --> 59:27.885
I'm doing piecework
for kids fresh out of school.

59:27.952 --> 59:30.254
You whip up a crowd
against me like that ever again,

59:30.320 --> 59:31.622
I'm gonna take your big idea,

59:31.688 --> 59:33.056
I'll throw it
on the fuckin' scrap heap.

59:33.123 --> 59:35.125
- Is that what you want?
- No, no.

59:35.192 --> 59:37.728
Okay, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

59:37.794 --> 59:39.530
None of that matters.

59:39.596 --> 59:42.099
Just read it.

59:43.934 --> 59:45.235
I'll read it.

59:46.971 --> 59:49.506
<i>What makes a person
go against their own brother?</i>

59:50.641 --> 59:52.209
<i>All my life,
I'd never had a family,</i>

59:52.276 --> 59:53.810
<i>so I never could
understand people</i>

59:53.877 --> 59:56.346
<i>who did and let it get ugly.</i>

59:56.413 --> 01:00:00.317
<i>My crazy brain was tellin' me I
should keep pullin' on that thread,</i>

01:00:00.384 --> 01:00:01.718
<i>but whatever Frank found,</i>

01:00:01.785 --> 01:00:03.620
<i>he found it
following the girl.</i>

01:00:03.687 --> 01:00:06.290
<i>So, I just kept chasin'
his footsteps.</i>

01:01:03.914 --> 01:01:05.115
Hello?

01:01:07.085 --> 01:01:08.285
Hello?

01:01:36.546 --> 01:01:37.547
If!

01:01:39.349 --> 01:01:41.218
Keep it together, Freakshow.

01:01:48.859 --> 01:01:49.860
Jesus.

01:01:52.763 --> 01:01:54.765
- You lookin' for somethin'?
- Help, Bailey!

01:01:54.831 --> 01:01:56.100
Ah, shit.

01:01:56.166 --> 01:01:57.367
What, you think you can just
walk into people's homes?

01:01:57.434 --> 01:01:58.769
No, I was lookin' for someone.

01:01:58.835 --> 01:02:00.038
I didn't think
anybody lived here.

01:02:00.104 --> 01:02:01.204
Oh, someone lives here.

01:02:01.271 --> 01:02:02.439
- My momma lives here.
- Sure.

01:02:02.506 --> 01:02:04.207
- At least, she's tryin' to.
- If!

01:02:04.274 --> 01:02:05.509
Who you with?

01:02:05.575 --> 01:02:07.011
- Huh?
- I hope you're with Belmont.

01:02:07.078 --> 01:02:08.879
Yeah, yeah, Belmont.
Who else?

01:02:13.283 --> 01:02:14.584
What is going on?

01:02:14.651 --> 01:02:16.453
We got ourselves
an intruder.

01:02:17.989 --> 01:02:20.290
- How hard did you hit him?
- I barely tapped him.

01:02:20.357 --> 01:02:21.725
Fool slipped
and hit his own head.

01:02:21.792 --> 01:02:22.793
If!

01:02:23.760 --> 01:02:25.595
"If" what?

01:02:25.662 --> 01:02:27.431
I'll tell you what, "if"...

01:02:27.497 --> 01:02:29.133
you better explain who you are

01:02:29.199 --> 01:02:30.734
if you want to
walk out of here.

01:02:32.335 --> 01:02:33.537
Have I seen you before?

01:02:33.603 --> 01:02:35.039
Yeah,
my name is Jake Gleason.

01:02:35.106 --> 01:02:36.140
It's a misunderstanding,
all right?

01:02:36.206 --> 01:02:37.741
I'm a reporter.

01:02:37.808 --> 01:02:40.410
I was at the Hamilton Housing
hearing the other night.

01:02:40.477 --> 01:02:42.046
I called the committee
this morning.

01:02:42.113 --> 01:02:43.880
I came out here
looking for you.

01:02:43.947 --> 01:02:46.483
He the one that said he's with
those racketeering sons of bitches.

01:02:46.550 --> 01:02:48.019
They stole her fridge.

01:02:48.086 --> 01:02:50.754
They stole her copper pipes.
Man, what you expect?

01:02:50.821 --> 01:02:53.390
First, they put up a notice says
the house will be condemned.

01:02:53.457 --> 01:02:55.225
It's not true,
but that scares out

01:02:55.292 --> 01:02:56.860
about half
and they sell for cheap.

01:02:56.927 --> 01:02:59.362
Then they come in and take
the nice old family homes,

01:02:59.429 --> 01:03:01.165
chop 'em into four
and rent 'em up.

01:03:01.231 --> 01:03:03.000
Folks who don't leave,
they harass,

01:03:03.067 --> 01:03:04.568
turn the heat off,

01:03:04.634 --> 01:03:06.770
come in to do repairs
and steal copper pipe instead.

01:03:06.837 --> 01:03:10.307
The city sold property worth
$15 million for 500,000

01:03:10.373 --> 01:03:13.243
to take the risk of having to
build the federal projects.

01:03:13.310 --> 01:03:14.845
They haven't even
submitted plans,

01:03:14.911 --> 01:03:16.913
just milked it
till it really is a slum.

01:03:16.981 --> 01:03:18.915
Slammer for the slum lords,
Bailey!

01:03:18.983 --> 01:03:20.484
- Ah...
- Oh, what?

01:03:20.550 --> 01:03:22.019
You're one of those who thinks
we're just agitating?

01:03:22.086 --> 01:03:24.421
Making it up like some
Negro propaganda conspiracy?

01:03:24.488 --> 01:03:26.356
No, no, look, look, look.
I got a condition, okay?

01:03:26.423 --> 01:03:29.526
It makes me say funny things,
but I'm not trying to be funny.

01:03:29.593 --> 01:03:30.995
I'm really not. I'm listenin'.

01:03:31.996 --> 01:03:33.296
Where's everybody go?

01:03:33.363 --> 01:03:37.101
Mostly just disappear.
Fade away.

01:03:37.168 --> 01:03:38.735
200,000 in two years,

01:03:38.802 --> 01:03:40.704
just from this part
of Brooklyn.

01:03:40.771 --> 01:03:43.007
- Mostly Negro. Latino.
- Yeah,

01:03:43.074 --> 01:03:44.841
but Horowitz said they did it
up in East Tremont, too.

01:03:44.908 --> 01:03:46.576
- Same thing?
- Yeah, they did it

01:03:46.643 --> 01:03:48.879
to a few Jews, too,
but not systematic like this.

01:03:48.945 --> 01:03:50.514
How many parks, do you think,
have been built

01:03:50.580 --> 01:03:52.549
in this city since
he's been commissioner?

01:03:52.616 --> 01:03:54.317
255.

01:03:54.384 --> 01:03:56.787
How many of those in Harlem,
you think?

01:03:57.621 --> 01:03:58.688
One.

01:03:58.755 --> 01:04:01.159
You build a new beach
for the people,

01:04:01.225 --> 01:04:02.459
but the ones with no cars,

01:04:02.526 --> 01:04:03.894
the poor ones,
the black and brown ones,

01:04:03.961 --> 01:04:06.130
how are they gonna get
to the parks and beaches?

01:04:06.197 --> 01:04:07.965
Public bus.

01:04:08.032 --> 01:04:11.768
Guess how high they just built
the overpasses on the new parkway?

01:04:11.835 --> 01:04:14.604
One foot too low
for a bus to clear.

01:04:14.671 --> 01:04:15.772
Come on.

01:04:15.839 --> 01:04:17.507
Look, forget whether
it's discrimination.

01:04:17.574 --> 01:04:19.110
The federal government and
the city are being scammed.

01:04:19.177 --> 01:04:21.378
There's supposed to be
relocation services,

01:04:21.444 --> 01:04:23.047
company's got
a $2 million contract

01:04:23.114 --> 01:04:25.348
to handle it, but nobody
even answers the phone.

01:04:25.415 --> 01:04:26.917
Call the city,
they say these folks

01:04:26.984 --> 01:04:28.585
are on the list for
the new public housing,

01:04:28.652 --> 01:04:29.954
- but then it never gets built.
- You know more

01:04:30.021 --> 01:04:31.555
than any secretary
I ever met in my life.

01:04:31.621 --> 01:04:34.258
Secretary? Who told you that?

01:04:34.324 --> 01:04:35.892
I got a law degree, you know?

01:04:35.960 --> 01:04:38.229
I'll pass the bar
first time I sit, too.

01:04:38.296 --> 01:04:40.097
Okay, then. Sorry.

01:04:40.164 --> 01:04:41.698
How are you gonna write about it
all if you don't even take a note?

01:04:41.765 --> 01:04:43.500
What, "$2 million
for relocation services,

01:04:43.567 --> 01:04:45.069
bridges a foot too low
for the buses,

01:04:45.136 --> 01:04:46.570
one out of 255 parks,

01:04:46.636 --> 01:04:48.438
15 million in property
for 500K,

01:04:48.505 --> 01:04:51.675
200,000 people
in Fort Greene alone." That?

01:04:51.741 --> 01:04:53.543
I never forget anything,
believe me.

01:04:53.610 --> 01:04:55.046
Not a single word.

01:04:56.981 --> 01:04:59.951
I'm really sorry.
I can't help it, I got a...

01:05:00.017 --> 01:05:01.319
It's okay.

01:05:01.384 --> 01:05:04.055
Just write about it, please.

01:05:04.121 --> 01:05:05.722
What happens to poor people
in this city

01:05:05.789 --> 01:05:08.226
wasn't news yesterday
and it won't be tomorrow,

01:05:08.292 --> 01:05:11.528
but you'd think somebody'd
care what happens to Brooklyn.

01:05:11.595 --> 01:05:13.897
It's only the biggest city
on Earth.

01:05:16.900 --> 01:05:17.934
Where you live?

01:05:19.203 --> 01:05:21.005
- Harlem.
- Hmm.

01:05:21.072 --> 01:05:23.007
This is me.

01:05:23.074 --> 01:05:24.741
You want me
to give you a ride?

01:05:26.344 --> 01:05:27.377
Come on,
the trains will be mobbed.

01:05:27.444 --> 01:05:28.645
I'll give you a ride.

01:05:29.913 --> 01:05:30.914
Come on.

01:06:01.945 --> 01:06:05.016
Bebop, Bailey, in the
Metropolitan Bopera House!

01:06:05.082 --> 01:06:06.816
Oh, God.

01:06:06.883 --> 01:06:09.353
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:06:09.419 --> 01:06:11.721
Don't be sorry.
It's kinda funny.

01:06:11.788 --> 01:06:15.825
Yeah? Well, hang around a little
while, and see what you think.

01:06:20.197 --> 01:06:21.198
If!

01:06:22.133 --> 01:06:23.700
What is all that, anyway?

01:06:23.767 --> 01:06:27.071
I don't know.
I never got a name for it.

01:06:27.138 --> 01:06:29.706
It's like a piece in my head broke
off and got a life of its own

01:06:29.773 --> 01:06:32.809
and then just decided to
keep joyridin' me for kicks.

01:06:33.443 --> 01:06:35.478
Kicks and tics!

01:06:35.545 --> 01:06:38.115
- Licks and tics!
- Sorry.

01:06:38.182 --> 01:06:39.482
It's okay.

01:06:39.549 --> 01:06:42.353
It's like living
with an anarchist, you know,

01:06:42.420 --> 01:06:46.257
but the funny thing is, it also has
to have everything in its right place.

01:06:46.324 --> 01:06:50.294
Like, things have to be ordered
and lined up just right.

01:06:50.361 --> 01:06:53.197
Everything has to sound
just right or else it really,

01:06:53.264 --> 01:06:55.899
it'll really put me into knots
until I fix it.

01:06:55.967 --> 01:06:58.369
Like, I'm talkin' to you
right now, right?

01:06:58.436 --> 01:06:59.836
But that part of my head,

01:06:59.903 --> 01:07:02.605
it's worryin' that the bills
in my wallet

01:07:02.672 --> 01:07:04.408
aren't lined up all in
the right sequence,

01:07:04.474 --> 01:07:05.942
and it's sayin',

01:07:06.010 --> 01:07:07.345
"Stop talkin' to this girl,
and deal with this."

01:07:07.411 --> 01:07:09.146
It's not fair.

01:07:09.213 --> 01:07:12.984
Hey, we all got
our daily battles, right?

01:07:14.751 --> 01:07:16.187
Yeah, fair enough.

01:07:20.724 --> 01:07:22.093
Kiss her face all night,
Bailey!

01:07:22.159 --> 01:07:25.029
Oh, God.

01:07:26.197 --> 01:07:27.365
I'm...

01:07:27.431 --> 01:07:28.732
- I really am sorry.
- It's okay.

01:07:28.798 --> 01:07:30.968
- I don't mean nothin' by it.
- Don't be sorry.

01:07:31.035 --> 01:07:32.702
It's okay.

01:07:55.658 --> 01:07:57.128
This is me.

01:07:57.194 --> 01:07:59.430
What, up from that?
That must keep you up nights.

01:07:59.497 --> 01:08:01.664
My father owns the place.

01:08:01.731 --> 01:08:04.934
I grew up falling asleep
in the back of clubs.

01:08:05.002 --> 01:08:06.971
It's pretty hoppin'
for a Monday night.

01:08:07.038 --> 01:08:09.240
Hottest band in the world,
all week.

01:08:10.607 --> 01:08:12.109
Listen...

01:08:12.176 --> 01:08:15.079
I gotta check
on one or two things,

01:08:15.146 --> 01:08:18.548
but are you really interested
in what I was telling you?

01:08:19.649 --> 01:08:22.752
Yeah, I came lookin' for you,
didn't I?

01:08:22.819 --> 01:08:25.755
If you wanna come in,
I could give you a lot more.

01:08:27.924 --> 01:08:31.261
I don't tend to do so good
in places like this.

01:08:31.328 --> 01:08:33.064
Come on, you can't exactly
disturb the peace

01:08:33.130 --> 01:08:35.332
in a small club
with a hot band.

01:08:37.301 --> 01:08:38.301
All right.

01:08:39.502 --> 01:08:41.171
It's your party.

01:08:48.678 --> 01:08:50.481
Keep an eye on it
for me, all right?

01:08:59.523 --> 01:09:00.790
Hey, Vance.

01:09:10.334 --> 01:09:11.969
Hey, you, out.

01:09:14.770 --> 01:09:16.173
- Hey, George.
- Hey, girl.

01:09:16.240 --> 01:09:17.241
Welcome.

01:09:19.542 --> 01:09:20.877
I'll be right back.

01:09:21.979 --> 01:09:22.979
If!

01:09:24.482 --> 01:09:27.051
Excuse me? Sir?

01:09:27.118 --> 01:09:29.618
I'm sorry. Um...
I'm a player, too.

01:09:29.685 --> 01:09:30.955
And, you know what, man?

01:09:31.020 --> 01:09:33.256
I really, really admire
your tremolo.

01:09:33.323 --> 01:09:34.524
And I'm just curious,

01:09:34.591 --> 01:09:37.627
how did you develop
that tremolo?

01:09:37.694 --> 01:09:40.363
Suckin' off little
white boys like you.

01:09:40.430 --> 01:09:42.433
Get the fuck out of here.

01:09:42.500 --> 01:09:44.969
So what?
Whitey White suck stick!

01:09:45.902 --> 01:09:47.636
"So what" is right.

01:10:03.753 --> 01:10:05.189
Listen to me. Listen!

01:10:05.256 --> 01:10:06.991
<i>How y'all doin' this evenin'?</i>

01:10:07.057 --> 01:10:08.492
<i>Feels good to be home
with friends and family.</i>

01:10:08.559 --> 01:10:10.194
<i>I been travelin' the world,</i>

01:10:11.428 --> 01:10:14.165
<i>learnin' new languages...</i>

01:10:14.231 --> 01:10:17.301
<i>and with new language
comes new ideas.</i>

01:10:17.368 --> 01:10:20.371
<i>So, we gonna try a few of them
on y'all tonight.</i>

01:10:20.437 --> 01:10:21.804
<i>Strap in.</i>

01:10:31.748 --> 01:10:33.050
If! Oh.

01:10:33.117 --> 01:10:34.985
You sure you don't wanna
sit in the back?

01:10:35.052 --> 01:10:36.287
Vance?

01:10:39.822 --> 01:10:41.425
Trumpet player's a jazzmatazz!

01:10:43.093 --> 01:10:46.330
Can we just sit in the back?
Let's sit in the back.

01:10:46.397 --> 01:10:47.730
No one cares.

01:10:58.542 --> 01:10:59.977
Ah!

01:11:01.579 --> 01:11:04.048
It's better 'cause I can
control what's on it.

01:11:04.114 --> 01:11:06.283
Okay, you need
to get out more.

01:11:11.155 --> 01:11:12.156
Oh!

01:11:29.607 --> 01:11:31.874
- You wanna get up there?
- No, I don't. I don't.

01:11:31.941 --> 01:11:34.211
It's causin' me problems.

01:11:56.667 --> 01:11:57.900
Don't put your hands on me.

01:11:57.968 --> 01:12:00.337
There she is,
my favorite baby girl,

01:12:00.404 --> 01:12:02.673
looking pretty as a rose.

01:12:02.740 --> 01:12:04.774
This next one's for you,
Laura.

01:12:30.734 --> 01:12:32.670
I don't think
I can do this. It's not...

01:12:32.736 --> 01:12:34.538
It's okay. It's okay.

01:12:38.875 --> 01:12:41.512
If!
It's not a good idea.

01:13:47.378 --> 01:13:48.512
Where is she?

01:14:41.064 --> 01:14:43.066
I'm just gonna deal
with something.

01:14:52.810 --> 01:14:54.011
What's goin' on?

01:14:54.077 --> 01:14:55.345
All right, y'all,
don't get too cozy.

01:14:55.412 --> 01:14:57.881
That was your last break.

01:15:12.362 --> 01:15:13.363
Oh!

01:15:15.065 --> 01:15:16.066
If!

01:15:32.082 --> 01:15:34.218
Oh! Hey!

01:15:34.284 --> 01:15:36.320
Hey, take it easy,
take it easy!

01:15:37.087 --> 01:15:39.256
Jesus, what'd I do?

01:15:40.824 --> 01:15:42.092
I said, let's go!

01:15:42.159 --> 01:15:43.293
Tell it
to the fuckin' judge!

01:15:43.360 --> 01:15:44.461
Take it easy.

01:15:44.528 --> 01:15:47.030
- Shut up!
- Hey, I got this.

01:15:49.233 --> 01:15:51.134
You think I don't know
who you work for, cracker?

01:15:51.201 --> 01:15:52.569
Black cracker,
crack-whacker!

01:15:52.636 --> 01:15:54.404
Hey... I made it through
Iwo Jima, motherfucker!

01:15:54.471 --> 01:15:55.873
You think your boss scares me?

01:15:55.939 --> 01:15:57.341
Now you tell him that if I see

01:15:57.407 --> 01:15:58.675
any of you snoops
around her again,

01:15:58.742 --> 01:16:00.911
I will kill you off
one at a time,

01:16:00.979 --> 01:16:03.714
and I will mail what he's
lookin' for to the <i>Post</i> for free!

01:16:03.780 --> 01:16:06.483
Do you hear me?
I will mail it to the <i>Post!</i>

01:16:07.918 --> 01:16:09.119
Let's go.

01:16:11.221 --> 01:16:12.589
If!

01:16:12.656 --> 01:16:13.657
If!

01:16:29.540 --> 01:16:31.241
Meow, the tomcat!

01:16:32.075 --> 01:16:34.044
Scarlet, the scared cat!

01:16:41.285 --> 01:16:42.586
Trumpet, my man!

01:16:46.690 --> 01:16:47.824
Hep cat needs help!

01:16:48.825 --> 01:16:50.227
Help for the hep cat!

01:16:51.562 --> 01:16:53.931
You were pretty hep in there
tonight yourself, cat.

01:16:53.998 --> 01:16:55.098
Help!

01:16:55.165 --> 01:16:56.767
The hep cat needs help!

01:17:02.172 --> 01:17:03.373
If!

01:17:07.210 --> 01:17:09.780
What, your head need fixin',
too?

01:17:09.846 --> 01:17:11.214
- Yeah.
- Oh, whoa, whoa.

01:17:11.281 --> 01:17:14.018
Wait, now, this ain't
just no marijuana.

01:17:14.084 --> 01:17:15.485
It's all right.

01:17:48.819 --> 01:17:50.621
You remember what I said.

01:18:15.046 --> 01:18:16.313
Oh, God.

01:18:17.681 --> 01:18:18.682
Shit.

01:18:19.683 --> 01:18:21.385
Sorry.

01:18:21.451 --> 01:18:23.720
Sorry, I don't even know
what happened.

01:18:23.787 --> 01:18:25.856
You had a good time,
that's what happened.

01:18:26.890 --> 01:18:28.392
Had a little party.

01:18:28.458 --> 01:18:31.595
Different mix of people
than the usual.

01:18:31.662 --> 01:18:35.532
She called it
a <i>étrange mélange.</i>

01:18:36.600 --> 01:18:37.901
Thought you could
use some rest,

01:18:37.969 --> 01:18:40.470
so we just let you be.

01:18:40.537 --> 01:18:42.006
Oh!

01:18:42.073 --> 01:18:43.373
Yeah.

01:18:43.440 --> 01:18:44.641
That guy left his footprint
on my ribs,

01:18:44.708 --> 01:18:46.309
I remember that part.

01:18:46.376 --> 01:18:48.211
Thanks for bailin' me
out of there.

01:18:48.278 --> 01:18:50.714
Sarge is a good man,

01:18:50.781 --> 01:18:53.450
but you gotta watch how you
are around a man's family,

01:18:53.517 --> 01:18:54.785
you know what I'm sayin'?

01:18:54.851 --> 01:18:55.852
Who's Sarge?

01:18:55.919 --> 01:18:57.989
- Billy.
- Why you call him "Sarge"?

01:18:58.056 --> 01:19:00.457
You don't know how he got
his arm all fucked up?

01:19:00.524 --> 01:19:02.693
- Mmm-mmm.
- Colored Marine Unit,

01:19:02.759 --> 01:19:03.794
carryin' ammo,

01:19:03.860 --> 01:19:05.362
and one day,
he picked up a gun

01:19:05.429 --> 01:19:08.699
tryin' to stop a Jap
suicide attack, got hit.

01:19:08.765 --> 01:19:11.535
Came back from that war
bitter as hell.

01:19:11.601 --> 01:19:13.904
Damn shame, too,
'cause he could play.

01:19:14.805 --> 01:19:15.739
Trombone.

01:19:15.806 --> 01:19:17.407
- Hmm.
- He used to jam with us

01:19:17.474 --> 01:19:19.876
down at Minton's
back in the '40s.

01:19:21.012 --> 01:19:23.147
You ever met his wife?

01:19:23.213 --> 01:19:24.614
Sarge ain't never married.

01:19:24.681 --> 01:19:26.184
What about Laura's mother?

01:19:26.249 --> 01:19:28.186
I don't know nothin'
about that.

01:19:28.251 --> 01:19:30.088
It was just Laura and him.

01:19:30.154 --> 01:19:31.855
She was a tiny little thing,

01:19:31.922 --> 01:19:34.891
always in the kitchen,
readin' while we was playin'.

01:19:36.160 --> 01:19:37.661
You play?

01:19:37.728 --> 01:19:40.263
- Music? No.
- Now, I'm not so keen

01:19:40.330 --> 01:19:42.833
on people bein' vocal
while we playin'...

01:19:44.168 --> 01:19:46.137
but you was on the line.

01:19:46.204 --> 01:19:47.537
I could hear it.

01:19:47.604 --> 01:19:49.974
On the line, Lionel.
Lionel's on the line.

01:19:50.041 --> 01:19:51.808
Sorry, I...

01:19:51.875 --> 01:19:54.811
I got somethin' wrong
with my head...

01:19:54.878 --> 01:19:58.248
and the music really, really
set it off. I'm sorry.

01:19:58.315 --> 01:19:59.649
Don't be sorry.

01:19:59.716 --> 01:20:02.153
You got a head
just like mine,

01:20:02.220 --> 01:20:04.821
always boilin' over.

01:20:04.888 --> 01:20:06.690
Turnin' things around.

01:20:07.891 --> 01:20:08.892
But that's music.

01:20:08.960 --> 01:20:11.095
Controls you
more than you control it,

01:20:11.162 --> 01:20:12.496
once it gets in you.

01:20:12.562 --> 01:20:13.897
Some people call it a gift,

01:20:13.965 --> 01:20:15.866
but it's a brain affliction
just the same.

01:20:15.932 --> 01:20:17.801
Yeah, well,
I just twitch and shout.

01:20:17.868 --> 01:20:20.238
At least you got a horn
to push it through,

01:20:20.303 --> 01:20:22.039
